  "body": "This is related to #1242 \r\n\r\nI find projects that I try to contribute to frequently use wildcard paths. \r\nWhile this works for Unix systems, it does not work in Windows. \r\n\r\nExample from a `package.json` in a project using hardhat:\r\n```\r\n\"test:hardhat\": \"hardhat test \\\"test/*.spec.ts\\\"\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nI had a read of the discord chat and it appears this feature isn't a priority, but I still believe it will be a valuable change. \r\n",
