    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Scripts defined in `package.json` get expanded by a shell process, so you can just change the above to:\r\n\r\n    \"test:hardhat\": \"hardhat test test/*.spec.ts\"\r\n\r\nand it will work; there's no need for hardhat to do the expansion when the shell will do it.\r\n\r\n`npx hardhat test test/*.spec.ts` from the CLI will work for the same reason.\r\n\r\nIdeally it would also be possible to dictate which tests get run via the hardhat or mocha config files, but unfortunately that doesn't work either; I've submitted #1806 to track that.",
